KATSINA – The 2022 Batch A stream 1 corps members in Katsina have been urged to observe and maintain the core values of the NYSC service scheme to achieve its objectives in nation-building. A former Anambra State Coordinator of the NYSC, Mr. Chinedu John Elabor gave the charge while addressing the corps members at the orientation camp in Katsina. Elabor said the core values of the scheme include, Loyalty, Integrity, Efficiency, Commitment and teamwork meant to inculcate discipline into Nigerian youths, raise their morales in line with national development and bring them together among others. Yobe: DG NYSC Cautions Corp Members On Discipline 2019: INEC, CSOs Disagree Over Use Of Corps Members As Electoral… The former NYSC boss noted that the NYSC scheme came into existence through decree no 24 of 22nd May 1973 in response to the consequences of the country’s civil war as part of the federal government post-war policy of Reconciliation, Rehabilitation and Reconstruction (3Rs). He added that the then military government found it paramount to introduce such a platform that will galvanize Nigerian youths, give them knowledge, discipline and National integration as well as harmonize them to ensure a free and detribalized nation. He however urged them to make proper use of the literature they have been given to read and to take their CDS and SAEDs in camp training very serious to enable them to reap their benefits.